
	Kosmos Energy said it would plug one of its exploration wells offshore Mauritania after it failed to find significant amount of oil and gas. 
	Evaluation of logs and samples collected during drillingand wireline operations suggests the Campanian reservoir objective was water-bearing with some residual hydrocarbons, Kosmos said. 
	"We are still in the early stages of exploring this newly emerging basin and our forward drilling program remains unchanged given the independent nature of the prospects," Chief Executive Andrew Inglis said in a statement.Â 